<TITLE> 3 buried in Bhola </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhola, June 5 (bdnews24.com)  Three people who perished in Thursday night's tragic fire disaster at Dhaka's Nimtali area have been laid to rest at Bhola. They were identified as Abdullah-Al-Mamun Shohag, 32, his wife Yeasmin Rashid Ruma, 27, and their only son Rafi, 7, residents of Jamiralata village of Bhola sadar. The bodies were buried at 1am on Friday, in their family graveyard. Before that at around 11pm, the three bodies were sent to their village by road. Heart-rending scenes ensued as the family received the dead bodies. Shohag's parents looked on in devastated silence as three were buried. Shohag's uncle advocate Mohammad Alauddin told bdnews24.com that he (Shohag) was appointed as a driver in the Unilever Company in Dhaka, six months ago. Shohagand his family shifted at Nimtali two months ago. bdnews24.
